===Etymology 1===
{{OE.}} ''[[scite]]'' ‘dung’, ''[[scitte]]'' ‘diarrhoea’, from {{Ger.}} ''*skit-'', from {{IE.}} ''*skheid-'' ‘to split, divide, separate’. Related to Middle Low German [[schite]], Middle Dutch [[schitte]]. Compare [[shite]].

